Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.41,0:00:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well... you've found\Nsome wonderful property.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.22,0:00:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a convenient twenty-minute drive\Nfrom the center of Berlin;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.86,0:00:11.99,Monster - Time and Place,,0,0,0,,{\pos(365,260)\fad(712,635)}Former
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.86,0:00:11.99,Monster - Time and Place,,0,0,0,,{\pos(365,310)\fad(712,635)}(East Berlin)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.59,0:00:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in a well-located\Nand nice neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.89,0:00:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rare to find this sort of property\Non the former East side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.90,0:00:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't this the residence\Nof Mr. Liebert,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.94,0:00:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the consultant to the former\NEast German Trade Commission?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.54,0:00:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.94,0:00:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You just came\Nto investigate Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all?! You're not a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... There was something\NI just had to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.65,0:00:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know anything about\Nan official who died ten years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.56,0:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lieberts adopted twins\Nwhile they were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.36,0:00:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I don't know anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.87,0:00:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the landlord?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.60,0:00:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you introduce me to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.47,0:00:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen... most of the land in\Nthe former East side is the property
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.61,0:01:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jewish capitalists who escaped\Nfrom the Nazi regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.91,0:01:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The eastern government was paying\Nforeign countries and capitalists
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from the west side\Nand borrowing land.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.42,0:01:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The landlord for this property\Nis overseas...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.88,0:01:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, my company is\Na west-side real estate company
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.22,0:01:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that prospered after\Nthe destruction of the Wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.59,0:01:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.33,0:01:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, get out.\NI'm going to lock the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.73,0:01:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anyone who knows\Nabout ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.03,0:01:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who\Nremembers Mr. Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.74,0:01:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As I told you, this is a residential area\Nfor ex-government officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.54,0:01:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Most fled after the Wall came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially from the officials from\Nthe Ministry of the Interior...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.45,0:01:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,An ex-official of the former East German\NDepartment of Commerce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,lives ten houses away from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mr. Liebert. He didn't have to\Ntake such a risk, only to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If only he had waited\Njust a little longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:01:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,until East Germany collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.17,0:02:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder why\Nhe went to a free country...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.00,0:02:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to be killed of all things...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.87,0:02:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Liebert have twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.61,0:02:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.21,0:02:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.32,0:02:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Those twins that Mr. Liebert adopted\Nfrom the orphanage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.42,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Orphanage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.09,0:02:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They were such cute kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.39,0:02:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Liebert always wanted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.53,0:02:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Where is that orphanage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.73,0:02:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... 511?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right,\NI think it was 511 Kinderheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,511... Kinderheim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:14.79,Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,350)\fad(1017,918)}511 Kinderheim
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The site of this orphanage will soon\Nbe turned into a supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm relieved that this creepy building\Nis finally going to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, do you know anyone\Nfrom this orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.75,0:05:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.09,0:05:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.56,0:05:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really want to find out,\Nthere's Hartmann over on 47th St.,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.73,0:06:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who worked at the old\NMinistry of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.42,0:06:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there... Do you know someone\Nnamed Hartmann who lives around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.43,0:06:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.63,0:06:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're injured... Let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.87,0:06:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Don't be afraid.\NLet me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You've injured a healing wound...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's festering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.08,0:06:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Suck it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This will sting a little,\Nbut this will help you get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.59,0:06:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.93,0:07:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get hurt again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.14,0:07:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hartmann...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I became the foster parent to all those\Nkids after the fall of East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.83,0:07:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Foster parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I took care of them until they\Nwere adopted or went off on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.74,0:07:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The president of\Nan accessories company
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted the kid in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.38,0:07:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid to the left\Nis in the military right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.58,0:07:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm even taking care of one right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:07:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:07:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't call it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.82,0:08:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked for many years,\Ndealing with orphans,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.33,0:08:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as the district official for\Nthe Ministry of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.59,0:08:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I opposed the way that the government\Nwas treating them at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.33,0:08:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of socialism, I wanted to\Nhelp the children in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm poor and things\Nhaven't gone my way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.54,0:08:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but, still, it's much better than\Nthe orphanages that they were in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.95,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,511 Kinderheim was\Na special orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that was run by both\Nthe Ministry of Health and Welfare
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all orphanages in East Germany\Nwere more or less like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.26,0:08:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but special orphanages\Nwere the worst of them all...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just an institution\Nfor children with nowhere to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.87,0:08:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a gathering for\Nthe children of criminals,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.98,0:08:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,captured political offenders,\Nand the children of those
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,suspected of being rebels and spies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it was expected that\Nthey would be discriminated against
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and treated inhumanely...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.92,0:09:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The children there couldn't do\Nanything about their situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a clash between socialism\Nand totalitarianism...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.33,0:09:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The government told the public that\Nthe orphans would be reeducated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.80,0:09:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and turned into model socialists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.74,0:09:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality,\Nthey were treated like criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.11,0:09:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The directors and instructors\Nwere horrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.45,0:09:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst ones would confiscate\Npackages sent to the children
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.85,0:09:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Who were the real criminals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.25,0:09:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear and violence ruled\Nthe special orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.96,0:09:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No person would grow up\Nnormal there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that incident happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.17,0:09:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Incident?\NWhat happened at that orphanage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:10:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that you wanted to\Nask me about the twins, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.14,0:10:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know something about them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.38,0:10:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know much about the sister\Nbecause she was left at an orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.68,0:10:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different district.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do know about\Nthe brother, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.35,0:10:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan! Yes, I want to\Nknow about Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was... It was top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.97,0:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The East German government\Nplaced a strict gag order on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.01,0:10:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's all right to talk about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this incident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.52,0:10:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What did... What did Johan do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A revolt...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.86,0:10:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.37,0:11:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, we have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Come and greet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.14,0:11:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what's with your attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.57,0:11:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to greet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.38,0:11:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's okay. We already met\Nin front of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I'd like to hear the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.59,0:11:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.69,0:11:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in front of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.89,0:11:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.59,0:11:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already late so we should\Nmeet another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.90,0:11:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.10,0:11:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you care to\Nhave dinner with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.91,0:11:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tenma, you say that\Nyou're a freelance journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.82,0:11:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that you're going to\Nwrite an article about the things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.62,0:11:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've investigated?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.32,0:11:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.16,0:11:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, this is one thing\NI want you to emphasize...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.23,0:12:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The development of a child
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.46,0:12:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all depends on the adult\Nthat raises him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.17,0:12:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We must lead children\Nin the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.87,0:12:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when children can\Nhave pleasant dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.48,0:12:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams, huh-?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.28,0:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what dreams do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.58,0:12:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A soccer ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.95,0:12:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh--?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a soccer ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.99,0:12:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.19,0:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.89,0:12:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to continue where we left off\Nanother time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry we couldn't\Nfinish our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.30,0:12:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I can come tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:12:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.48,0:13:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.35,0:13:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.00,0:13:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.40,0:13:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.50,0:13:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.14,0:13:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Mr. Hartmann!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.84,0:13:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.84,0:13:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Mr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.85,0:14:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.95,0:14:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.05,0:14:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.75,0:14:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was standing on the chair and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.86,0:14:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow... ow, it hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.86,0:14:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it hurt, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.66,0:14:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann, call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.57,0:14:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What are all these scars?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.75,0:14:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.48,0:14:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.38,0:14:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Two ribs are broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And his clavicle is dislocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he get this injury\Nfrom falling off a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.49,0:14:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The ambulance will be here soon,\Nso it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.30,0:14:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are all these injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that it's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:14:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.60,0:15:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you touch those injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.74,0:15:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if you're a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.94,0:15:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.85,0:15:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.11,0:15:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I heard\Nthat name somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.42,0:15:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one wanted for murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This injury...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.46,0:15:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are all these injuries\Non his body from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.23,0:15:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevermind that... Shouldn't you\Nbe running away, Mr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.37,0:15:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I called the police\Nalong with the ambulance...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.97,0:15:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann! I'm asking you\Nhow Dieter got all these injuries!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't matter\Nto someone like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.34,0:15:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who's wanted for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.35,0:15:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as I expected from a fugitive.\NYou're very short-tempered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.59,0:15:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it? Did what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.69,0:15:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You were abusing Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.13,0:15:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Abusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.50,0:15:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say such ill willed things\Nabout me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you plan to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to take him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First murder, and now kidnapping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.51,0:16:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be caught even if you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, Dieter! I'm going to\Nget you to a hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid of the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.16,0:16:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be afraid of!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors will get you better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.77,0:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Hartmann always\Nmakes me better...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.28,0:16:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're covered in injuries...\NYou've never been to a hospital?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid... Right now,\Nthe world is full of bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I have to be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.89,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Hartmann tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.43,0:17:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The future is dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.91,0:17:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.44,0:17:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big lie that the world is dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.81,0:17:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.45,0:17:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.82,0:17:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here... A soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.45,0:17:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow will be... a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.13,0:17:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for coming at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right... But we're crowded with\Nemergency cases at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.14,0:17:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It might take a while\Nuntil we can see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.57,0:17:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you do something about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.57,0:17:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a very big accident.\N—The bus driver died instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.78,0:17:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to ask the truck driver about\Nthe circumstances of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He broke both his legs,\Nbut he can still talk, can't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.42,0:17:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to treat him first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.49,0:18:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Question him later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.02,0:18:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll be waiting here.\N—U-Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.13,0:18:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.73,0:18:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.03,0:18:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care of that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.43,0:18:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, please don't let anyone\Nleave with him other than myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the accident site cleaned up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.44,0:18:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's still backed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.82,0:18:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.65,0:18:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what to do with Dieter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I go to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:43.02,Monster - Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,300)}I don't know much about\NJohan's sister because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.13,0:18:45.79,Monster - Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,300)}she was left at an orphanage\Nin a different district.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.07,0:18:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A different orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.84,0:18:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a child that you\Nwant me to take in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.22,0:19:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who are you? Why are you\Ncoming here at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.92,0:19:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's an unreasonable request,\Nbut this kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.13,0:19:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that the kid is being abused.\NBut if I don't know who you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.83,0:19:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.93,0:19:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take in a child from\Nsomeone so suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm... could this be the orphanage\Nthat took care of Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Anna Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So Anna was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. How nostalgic...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Anna doing? Is she well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.23,0:19:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.46,0:19:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, she's going\Nto Heidelberg University...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. She's doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.23,0:19:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna was a nice girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.34,0:19:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew she was adopted by\NMr. Liebert of the Trade Commission
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.14,0:20:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,along with her twin brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.98,0:20:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.08,0:20:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Johan, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They were very close,\Nbut I felt sorry for them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.95,0:20:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when they were placed\Nin separate orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two were really alone\Nbefore they came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When they were taken into custody\Nnear the border of Czechoslovakia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.96,0:20:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they were holding hands\Nas they walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They both were shivering in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, Mr. Liebert only\Nwanted to adopt Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.51,0:20:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But Johan wouldn't go\Nwithout his sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.71,0:20:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, Anna got to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the conditions\Nof the orphanages
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of the east side were horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.92,0:20:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not like 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.92,0:20:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.77,0:21:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Inge, the bathroom isn't that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay? See?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.78,0:21:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.75,0:21:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all right...\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now... you can go to the bathroom\Nby yourself, can't you??
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.39,0:21:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Those kids really did not know\Na parent's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.80,0:21:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You only need love in order to\Ndevelop as a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.87,0:21:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, the orphanages of\Nthe east side were quite horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.71,0:21:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even this place was once referred to\Nas Orphanage 47.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.08,0:21:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did what we could\Nso we wouldn't be controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by the government,\Neven just a little
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.05,0:21:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to avoid becoming\Nlike 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.26,0:22:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a special orphanage\Nrun by both
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.06,0:22:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ministry of Health and Welfare\Nand the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.36,0:22:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.27,0:22:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.67,0:22:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The real state of affairs\Nwas being managed by
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.17,0:22:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.47,0:22:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That place was... East Germany's\Nexperimental laboratory...
